news.title: Home First Finance posts net profit of Rs 44.86 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Home First Finance's net-worth as on September 2021 was at Rs 1,463 crore. The company appointed Ashish Kumar Darji as chief risk officer and Dharmvir Singh as chief technology officer.

news.title: Delhi HC dismisses plea to regularise affluent unauthorised colonies
news.para: The court asked whether the affluent owners of properties were illiterate, poor or a downtrodden class as they sought to regularise unauthorised colonies like Sainik Farms, Mahendru Enclave and Anant Ram Dairy Colony here.

news.title: Emirati prosecutors investigating Dubai's Union Properties
news.para: The announcement by prosecutors renewed questions about the wider stability of Dubai's boom-and-bust real estate market, which saw Union Properties pile on some $2 billion of debt during the city-state's financial crisis over a decade ago.

news.title: Goa: NGPDA notifies adoption of Mapusa land use map, register
news.para: NGPDA initiated the process to prepare the land use map and register of Mapusa planning area in August 2020 and the final land use map and register was approved on October 13.

news.title: Canada's Cominar REIT to go private in $1.73 billion deal
news.para: The investor consortium, which includes FrontFour Capital Group, Artis Real Estate Investment Trust and partnerships managed by the Sandpiper Group, will acquire Cominar for C$11.75 in cash per unit, Canderel said in a statement on Sunday.

news.title: Chennai development body's fire safety plans remain on paper
news.para: The Chennai Metropolitan Development Authority’s (CMDA) official portal states that 43 MSBs have no objection certificates (NOC) pending with the department of fire and rescue services.

news.title: Delhi: Highrises get going on rainwater harvesting, residents still skeptical
news.para: The RWAs had all along argued that it was not technically feasible to create water harvesting pits in already built-up areas on their complexes for fear of weakening the foundations.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board seeks clarification on collector rates
news.para: The CHB officials have now sought clarification on collector rates of different categories at IT Park so that accordingly they can go ahead with the auction of hospital site.

news.title: BASIC Home Loan raises $3.5 million in series A funding
news.para: The company aims to disburse Rs 6,000 crore loans for next billion households over next 18 months. It plans to achieve a monthly loan disbursal run rate of Rs 200 crore and hire 300+ people in the workforce by March 2022.

news.title: UPPCB slaps Rs 16 lakh fine for violation of dust pollution norms
news.para: In Ghaziabad, penalties of Rs 5 lakh each have been imposed on two malls. Fines have also been imposed on a mall at Noida Sector 75, a hospital in Noida Sector 50, and two private plots in Noida Sector 1.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA plans to allot leftover IT plots to industry, institutions
news.para: The authority has identified about 40 leftover plots and plans to come up with an allotment scheme for them soon. More may be added to the scheme as the GNIDA is preparing a list of remaining IT plots.

news.title: The Ramco Cements posts net profit of Rs 519.12 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The Ramco Cements' net consolidated total revenue stood at Rs 1,510.33 crore in Q2 FY22, an increase of 18.6 per cent from Rs 1,273.47 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Rent of retail space up 11-17% in Delhi's upscale markets in July-Sept: Report
news.para: ​"Rentals inching back to pre-COVID levels as market activity strengthens," global property consultant Cushman and Wakefield (C&W) said in its report 'Marketbeat- Delhi-NCR, Retail Q3 2021' (July-September).

news.title: RMZ Corp appoints Avinash Sule as managing director
news.para: This second appointment comes at a time where the company plans to propel their current 67 million sq ft of real assets, valued at US $10 billion, to 87 million sq ft which will be valued at US $15 billion by 2026.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Suggestions for draft rehabilitation policy for slum dwellers can be submitted till Nov 3
news.para: The draft policy states that the policy is applicable only for encroacher/non-titleholders of the land, where displacement is proposed for involuntary resettlement.
